R Notebook

Note: All these models are built out of the PIE Chart data which has their answers flipped.

Setup

library(loo)
library(rstan)
library(rstanarm)
rstan_options(auto_write = TRUE)
options(mc.cores = parallel::detectCores())
kfold <- function(log_lik_heldout)  {
  library(matrixStats)
  logColMeansExp <- function(x) {
    # should be more stable than log(colMeans(exp(x)))
    S <- nrow(x)
    colLogSumExps(x) - log(S)
  }
  # See equation (20) of @VehtariEtAl2016
  pointwise <-  matrix(logColMeansExp(log_lik_heldout), ncol= 1)
  colnames(pointwise) <- "elpd"
  # See equation (21) of @VehtariEtAl2016
  elpd_kfold <- sum(pointwise)
  se_elpd_kfold <-  sqrt(ncol(log_lik_heldout) * var(pointwise))
  out <- list(
  pointwise = pointwise,
  elpd_kfold = elpd_kfold,
  se_elpd_kfold = se_elpd_kfold)
  structure(out, class = "loo")
}
random_subjectID <- sample(min(flipped_pie$subjectID):max(flipped_pie$subjectID), 1)
testData <- subset(flipped_pie, subjectID == random_subjectID)
trainData <- subset(flipped_pie, subjectID != random_subjectID)

Leave One Person Validation

1-segment Single Cycle Model: Fitting

log_lik_total_participant <- matrix(, nrow = 500, ncol = 1)
#Pick 5 random persons to leave  
random_subjectID <- sample(min(flipped_pie$subjectID):max(flipped_pie$subjectID), 5)
#Perform 5 fold cross validation
for(i in 1:5){
    #Segement your data by fold using the which() function 
    testData <- subset(flipped_pie, subjectID == random_subjectID[i])
    trainData <- subset(flipped_pie, subjectID != random_subjectID[i])
    flipped_pie_data_m = list(
      nt = length(trainData$correct_ans), 
      correct_ans_t = trainData$correct_ans/100, 
      response_t = trainData$flipped_ans/100, 
      kt = length(unique(trainData$subjectID)),
      participant_t = trainData$subjectID,
      nh = length(testData$correct_ans), 
      correct_ans_h = testData$correct_ans/100, 
      response_h = testData$flipped_ans/100, 
      kh = length(unique(testData$subjectID)),
      participant_h = testData$subjectID,
      k = max(flipped_pie$subjectID), 
      segments = 1
    )
    fit_obj <- stan(file = 'models/kfold_models/kfold_single_cycle_model.stan', data = flipped_pie_data_m, iter = 1000, chains = 1, verbose=TRUE)
    log_lik_single_cycle <- extract_log_lik(fit_obj, parameter_name = "log_lik_h")
    log_lik_single_cycle <- cbind(log_lik_total_participant, log_lik_single_cycle)
}

log_lik_total_participant <- matrix(, nrow = 500, ncol = 1)
  
#Pick 5 random persons to leave

#Perform 5 fold cross validation
for(i in 1:5){
    #Segement your data by fold using the which() function 
    testData <- subset(flipped_pie, subjectID == random_subjectID[i])
    trainData <- subset(flipped_pie, subjectID != random_subjectID[i])
    flipped_pie_data_m = list(
      nt = length(trainData$correct_ans), 
      correct_ans_t = trainData$correct_ans/100, 
      response_t = trainData$flipped_ans/100,

      correct_ans_h = testData$correct_ans/100, 
      response_h = testData$flipped_ans/100,

Weighted Cycles Model: Fitting

log_lik_total_participant <- matrix(, nrow = 500, ncol = 1)
  
#Pick 5 random persons to leave  
random_subjectID <- sample(min(flipped_pie$subjectID):max(flipped_pie$subjectID), 5)
#Perform 5 fold cross validation
for(i in 1:5){
    #Segement your data by fold using the which() function 
    testData <- subset(flipped_pie, subjectID == random_subjectID[i])
    trainData <- subset(flipped_pie, subjectID != random_subjectID[i])
    flipped_pie_data_m = list(
      nt = length(trainData$correct_ans), 
      correct_ans_t = trainData$correct_ans/100, 
      response_t = trainData$flipped_ans/100, 
      kt = length(unique(trainData$subjectID)),
      participant_t = trainData$subjectID,
      nh = length(testData$correct_ans), 
      correct_ans_h = testData$correct_ans/100, 
      response_h = testData$flipped_ans/100, 
      kh = length(unique(testData$subjectID)),
      participant_h = testData$subjectID,
      k = max(flipped_pie$subjectID), 
      segments = c(1,2,4), 
      number_segments = 3
    )
    fit_obj <- stan(file = 'models/kfold_models/kfold_weighted_cycles_model.stan', data = flipped_pie_data_m, iter = 1000, chains = 1, verbose=TRUE)
    log_lik <- extract_log_lik(fit_obj, parameter_name = "log_lik_h")
    log_lik_weighted_cycles_lpo <- cbind(log_lik_total_participant, log_lik)
}

1-segment Single Cycle Model: Fitting

log_lik_total_participant <- matrix(, nrow = 500, ncol = 1)
  
#Randomly shuffle the data
kfold_pie<-flipped_pie[sample(nrow(flipped_pie)),]
#Create 5 equally size folds
folds <- cut(seq(1,nrow(kfold_pie)),breaks=5,labels=FALSE)
#Perform 5 fold cross validation
for(i in 1:5){
    #Segement your data by fold using the which() function 
    testIndexes <- which(folds==i,arr.ind=TRUE)
    testData <- kfold_pie[testIndexes, ]
    trainData <- kfold_pie[-testIndexes, ]
    flipped_pie_data_m = list(
      nt = length(trainData$correct_ans), 
      correct_ans_t = trainData$correct_ans/100, 
      response_t = trainData$flipped_ans/100, 
      kt = length(unique(trainData$subjectID)),
      participant_t = trainData$subjectID,
      nh = length(testData$correct_ans), 
      correct_ans_h = testData$correct_ans/100, 
      response_h = testData$flipped_ans/100, 
      kh = length(unique(testData$subjectID)),
      participant_h = testData$subjectID,
      k = max(flipped_pie$subjectID), 
      segments = 1
    )
    fit_obj <- stan(file = 'models/kfold_models/kfold_single_cycle_model.stan', data = flipped_pie_data_m, iter = 1000, chains = 1, verbose=TRUE)
    log_lik_single_cycle <- extract_log_lik(fit_obj, parameter_name = "log_lik_h")
    log_lik_single_cycle <- cbind(log_lik_total_participant, log_lik_single_cycle)
}

4-segment Single Cycle Model: Fitting

log_lik_total_participant <- matrix(, nrow = 500, ncol = 1)
  
#Randomly shuffle the data
kfold_pie<-flipped_pie[sample(nrow(flipped_pie)),]
#Create 5 equally size folds
folds <- cut(seq(1,nrow(kfold_pie)),breaks=5,labels=FALSE)
#Perform 5 fold cross validation
for(i in 1:5){
    #Segement your data by fold using the which() function 
    testIndexes <- which(folds==i,arr.ind=TRUE)
    testData <- kfold_pie[testIndexes, ]
    trainData <- kfold_pie[-testIndexes, ]
    flipped_pie_data_m = list(
      nt = length(trainData$correct_ans), 
      correct_ans_t = trainData$correct_ans/100, 
      response_t = trainData$flipped_ans/100, 
      kt = length(unique(trainData$subjectID)),
      participant_t = trainData$subjectID,
      nh = length(testData$correct_ans), 
      correct_ans_h = testData$correct_ans/100, 
      response_h = testData$flipped_ans/100, 
      kh = length(unique(testData$subjectID)),
      participant_h = testData$subjectID,
      k = max(flipped_pie$subjectID), 
      segments = 4
    )
    fit_obj <- stan(file = 'models/kfold_models/kfold_single_cycle_model.stan', data = flipped_pie_data_m, iter = 1000, chains = 1, verbose=TRUE)
    log_lik_single_cycle_4 <- extract_log_lik(fit_obj, parameter_name = "log_lik_h")
    log_lik_single_cycle_4 <- cbind(log_lik_total_participant, log_lik_single_cycle_4)
}

Weighted Cycles Model: Fitting

log_lik_total_participant <- matrix(, nrow = 500, ncol = 1)
  
#Randomly shuffle the data
kfold_pie<-flipped_pie[sample(nrow(flipped_pie)),]

#Create 5 equally size folds
folds <- cut(seq(1,nrow(kfold_pie)),breaks=5,labels=FALSE)

#Perform 5 fold cross validation
for(i in 1:5){
    #Segement your data by fold using the which() function 
    testIndexes <- which(folds==i,arr.ind=TRUE)
    testData <- kfold_pie[testIndexes, ]
    trainData <- kfold_pie[-testIndexes, ]
    flipped_pie_data_m = list(
      nt = length(trainData$correct_ans), 
      correct_ans_t = trainData$correct_ans/100, 
      response_t = trainData$flipped_ans/100, 
      kt = length(unique(trainData$subjectID)),
      participant_t = trainData$subjectID,
      nh = length(testData$correct_ans), 
      correct_ans_h = testData$correct_ans/100, 
      response_h = testData$flipped_ans/100, 
      kh = length(unique(testData$subjectID)),
      participant_h = testData$subjectID,
      k = max(flipped_pie$subjectID), 
      segments = c(1,2,4), 
      number_segments = 3
    )
    fit_obj <- stan(file = 'models/kfold_models/kfold_weighted_cycles_model.stan', data = flipped_pie_data_m, iter = 1000, chains = 1, verbose=TRUE)
    log_lik <- extract_log_lik(fit_obj, parameter_name = "log_lik_h")
    log_lik_weighted_cycles <- cbind(log_lik_total_participant, log_lik)
}

 603 :         }
 604 : 
 605 :         lp_accum__.add(lp__);
 606 :         return lp_accum__.sum();

 608 :     } // log_prob()

 610 :     template <bool propto, bool jacobian, typename T_>
 611 :     T_ log_prob(Eigen::Matrix<T_,Eigen::Dynamic,1>& params_r,
 612 :                std::ostream* pstream = 0) const {
 613 :       std::vector<T_> vec_params_r;
 614 :       vec_params_r.reserve(params_r.size());
 615 :       for (int i = 0; i < params_r.size(); ++i)
 616 :         vec_params_r.push_back(params_r(i));
 617 :       std::vector<int> vec_params_i;
 618 :       return log_prob<propto,jacobian,T_>(vec_params_r, vec_params_i, pstream);
 619 :     }

 947 : 
 948 :     template <typename RNG>
 949 :     void write_array(RNG& base_rng,
 950 :                      Eigen::Matrix<double,Eigen::Dynamic,1>& params_r,
 951 :                      Eigen::Matrix<double,Eigen::Dynamic,1>& vars,
 952 :                      bool include_tparams = true,
 953 :                      bool include_gqs = true,
 954 :                      std::ostream* pstream = 0) const {
 955 :       std::vector<double> params_r_vec(params_r.size());
 956 :       for (int i = 0; i < params_r.size(); ++i)
 957 :         params_r_vec[i] = params_r(i);
 958 :       std::vector<double> vars_vec;
 959 :       std::vector<int> params_i_vec;
 960 :       write_array(base_rng,params_r_vec,params_i_vec,vars_vec,include_tparams,include_gqs,pstream);
 961 :       vars.resize(vars_vec.size());
 962 :       for (int i = 0; i < vars.size(); ++i)
 963 :         vars(i) = vars_vec[i];
 964 :     }

log_lik_total_participant <- matrix(, nrow = 500, ncol = 1)
  
#Randomly shuffle the data
kfold_pie<-flipped_pie[sample(nrow(flipped_pie)),]
#Create 5 equally size folds
folds <- cut(seq(1,nrow(kfold_pie)),breaks=5,labels=FALSE)
#Perform 5 fold cross validation
for(i in 1:5){
    #Segement your data by fold using the which() function 
    testIndexes <- which(folds==i,arr.ind=TRUE)
    testData <- kfold_pie[testIndexes, ]
    trainData <- kfold_pie[-testIndexes, ]
    flipped_pie_data_m = list(
      nt = length(trainData$correct_ans), 
      correct_ans_t = trainData$correct_ans/100, 
      response_t = trainData$flipped_ans/100, 
      kt = length(unique(trainData$subjectID)),
      participant_t = trainData$subjectID,
      nh = length(testData$correct_ans), 
      correct_ans_h = testData$correct_ans/100, 
      response_h = testData$flipped_ans/100, 
      kh = length(unique(testData$subjectID)),
      participant_h = testData$subjectID,
      k = max(flipped_pie$subjectID), 
      segments = c(1,2,4), 
      number_segments = 3
    )
    fit_obj <- stan(file = 'models/kfold_models/kfold_indv_wts_pooled_power_model.stan', data = flipped_pie_data_m, iter = 1000, chains = 1, verbose=TRUE)
    log_lik_indv_weight_pooled_power <- extract_log_lik(fit_obj, parameter_name = "log_lik_h")
    log_lik_indv_weight_pooled_power <- cbind(log_lik_total_participant, log_lik_indv_weight_pooled_power)
}

 687 :     T_ log_prob(Eigen::Matrix<T_,Eigen::Dynamic,1>& params_r,
 688 :                std::ostream* pstream = 0) const {
 689 :       std::vector<T_> vec_params_r;
 690 :       vec_params_r.reserve(params_r.size());

 692 :         vec_params_r.push_back(params_r(i));
 693 :       std::vector<int> vec_params_i;
 694 :       return log_prob<propto,jacobian,T_>(vec_params_r, vec_params_i, pstream);
 695 :     }

1062 :     template <typename RNG>
1063 :     void write_array(RNG& base_rng,
1064 :                      Eigen::Matrix<double,Eigen::Dynamic,1>& params_r,
1065 :                      Eigen::Matrix<double,Eigen::Dynamic,1>& vars,
1066 :                      bool include_tparams = true,
1067 :                      bool include_gqs = true,
1068 :                      std::ostream* pstream = 0) const {
1069 :       std::vector<double> params_r_vec(params_r.size());
1070 :       for (int i = 0; i < params_r.size(); ++i)
1071 :         params_r_vec[i] = params_r(i);
1072 :       std::vector<double> vars_vec;
1073 :       std::vector<int> params_i_vec;
1074 :       write_array(base_rng,params_r_vec,params_i_vec,vars_vec,include_tparams,include_gqs,pstream);
1075 :       vars.resize(vars_vec.size());
1076 :       for (int i = 0; i < vars.size(); ++i)
1077 :         vars(i) = vars_vec[i];
1078 :     }

#Remove NA Column
#log_lik_indv_weight_pooled_power <- log_lik_indv_weight_pooled_power[, -1]

Individual Weight Individual Power Model: Fitting

log_lik_total_participant <- matrix(, nrow = 500, ncol = 1)
  
#Randomly shuffle the data
kfold_pie<-flipped_pie[sample(nrow(flipped_pie)),]
#Create 5 equally size folds
folds <- cut(seq(1,nrow(kfold_pie)),breaks=5,labels=FALSE)
#Perform 5 fold cross validation
for(i in 1:5){
    #Segement your data by fold using the which() function 
    testIndexes <- which(folds==i,arr.ind=TRUE)
    testData <- kfold_pie[testIndexes, ]
    trainData <- kfold_pie[-testIndexes, ]
    flipped_pie_data_m = list(
      nt = length(trainData$correct_ans), 
      correct_ans_t = trainData$correct_ans/100, 
      response_t = trainData$flipped_ans/100, 
      kt = length(unique(trainData$subjectID)),
      participant_t = trainData$subjectID,
      nh = length(testData$correct_ans), 
      correct_ans_h = testData$correct_ans/100, 
      response_h = testData$flipped_ans/100, 
      kh = length(unique(testData$subjectID)),
      participant_h = testData$subjectID,
      k = max(flipped_pie$subjectID), 
      segments = c(1,2,4), 
      number_segments = 3
    )
    fit_obj <- stan(file = 'models/kfold_models/kfold_indv_wts_and_power_model.stan', data = flipped_pie_data_m, iter = 1000, chains = 1, verbose=TRUE)
    log_lik_indv_power_indv_weight <- extract_log_lik(fit_obj, parameter_name = "log_lik_h")
    log_lik_indv_power_indv_weight <- cbind(log_lik_total_participant, log_lik_indv_power_indv_weight)
}

 692 :     template <bool propto, bool jacobian, typename T_>
 693 :     T_ log_prob(Eigen::Matrix<T_,Eigen::Dynamic,1>& params_r,
 694 :                std::ostream* pstream = 0) const {
 695 :       std::vector<T_> vec_params_r;
 696 :       vec_params_r.reserve(params_r.size());
 697 :       for (int i = 0; i < params_r.size(); ++i)
 698 :         vec_params_r.push_back(params_r(i));
 699 :       std::vector<int> vec_params_i;
 700 :       return log_prob<propto,jacobian,T_>(vec_params_r, vec_params_i, pstream);
 701 :     }

1075 :     template <typename RNG>
1076 :     void write_array(RNG& base_rng,
1077 :                      Eigen::Matrix<double,Eigen::Dynamic,1>& params_r,
1078 :                      Eigen::Matrix<double,Eigen::Dynamic,1>& vars,
1079 :                      bool include_tparams = true,
1080 :                      bool include_gqs = true,
1081 :                      std::ostream* pstream = 0) const {
1082 :       std::vector<double> params_r_vec(params_r.size());
1083 :       for (int i = 0; i < params_r.size(); ++i)
1084 :         params_r_vec[i] = params_r(i);
1085 :       std::vector<double> vars_vec;
1086 :       std::vector<int> params_i_vec;
1087 :       write_array(base_rng,params_r_vec,params_i_vec,vars_vec,include_tparams,include_gqs,pstream);
1088 :       vars.resize(vars_vec.size());
1089 :       for (int i = 0; i < vars.size(); ++i)
1090 :         vars(i) = vars_vec[i];
1091 :     }
